

==================================================
GREEN SALADS
==================================================

1 Salade Verte (Simple Green Salad) — mixed lettuces with a basic vinaigrette; the foundation of all green salads.
2 Caesar Salad — romaine, Parmesan, croutons, and Caesar dressing (anchovy, garlic, egg yolk, lemon, olive oil).
3 Wedge Salad — iceberg wedge topped with blue cheese dressing, bacon, tomato, and chives.
4 Cobb Salad — chopped greens with chicken, bacon, egg, avocado, tomato, and blue cheese.
5 Niçoise Salad (Greens‑forward variant) — tuna, egg, olives, potatoes, green beans, and greens with vinaigrette.
6 Greek Salad (with lettuce in American style) — romaine or iceberg with tomato, cucumber, onion, olives, feta.
7 Spinach Salad with Warm Bacon Dressing — baby spinach, hard‑boiled egg, mushrooms, and hot bacon vinaigrette.
8 Frisée aux Lardons (Lyonnaise Salad) — frisée with bacon lardons, croutons, and a poached egg.
9 Arugula Salad with Parmesan and Lemon — peppery arugula dressed simply with citrus and cheese.
10 Kale Salad (Massaged Kale or Kale Caesar) — hearty kale leaves tenderized and dressed with bold vinaigrettes.
11 Endive and Walnut Salad — Belgian endive with walnuts, blue cheese, and vinaigrette.
12 Radicchio Salad — bitter radicchio balanced with sweet or creamy elements like honey, balsamic, or gorgonzola.
13 Watercress Salad — peppery watercress with citrus or mustard vinaigrette.
14 Escarole Salad — slightly bitter escarole paired with anchovy, lemon, or Parmesan.
15 Herb Salad — parsley, mint, basil, and chervil mixed with tender greens for a fragrant, delicate salad.
16 Composed Green Salads (restaurant‑style) — greens arranged with multiple toppings (e.g., avocado, roasted vegetables, nuts) for visual and textural balance.
17 Grilled Romaine or Radicchio Salad — charred greens dressed after grilling for smoky flavor.
18 Seasonal Foraged Green Salad (Mâche, Sorrel, Wild Greens) — delicate seasonal greens paired with light vinaigrettes.


==================================================
VEGETABLE SALADS
==================================================

1 Ratatouille salad — roasted Mediterranean vegetables (eggplant, zucchini, bell pepper, tomato) served room temperature with herbs.
2 Niçoise-style vegetable salad — composed plate highlighting tomatoes, green beans, potatoes, olives (often with tuna but can be purely vegetable).
3 Russian vinaigrette — diced beets, potatoes, carrots, pickles, and sauerkraut or peas dressed with oil and vinegar.
4 Greek salad (Horiatiki) — tomatoes, cucumbers, red onion, peppers, olives, and feta; simple herbaceous dressing.
5 Caprese salad — ripe tomatoes, fresh mozzarella, basil, olive oil and balsamic (focus on produce quality).
6 Panzanella — Tuscan bread salad with tomatoes, cucumbers, red onion and stale bread, dressed to soak.
7 Marinated grilled vegetable salad — grilled zucchini, eggplant, peppers, mushrooms marinated in vinaigrette.
8 Warm roasted cauliflower salad — caramelized cauliflower with lemon, capers, herbs, and often yogurt or tahini.
9 Roasted carrot salad — glazed or roasted carrots with citrus, herbs, nuts or seeds, and a bright dressing.
10 Beet and goat cheese salad — roasted or boiled beets with tangy cheese, nuts, and vinaigrette.
11 Tabbouleh — parsley-forward Levantine salad with bulgur, tomatoes, mint, lemon and olive oil.
12 Fattoush — Levantine mixed-vegetable salad with toasted pita, sumac, and a zesty dressing.
13 Cucumber salad (quick pickled or creamy dill) — thinly sliced cucumbers with vinegar or yogurt/dill dressing.
14 Coleslaw (classic and variations) — shredded cabbage with mayonnaise or vinegar-based dressing; many regional variants.
15 Braised fennel salad — thinly sliced raw or roasted fennel with citrus and Parmesan.
16 Shaved asparagus salad — thin asparagus ribbons with lemon, Parmesan, and olive oil (often raw in spring).
17 Grilled romesco vegetable salad — vegetables finished with romesco sauce (roasted red pepper, nuts, garlic).
18 Escabeche vegetable salad — pickled/poached vegetables in spiced vinegar (Spanish/Latin styles).
19 Carpaccio of root vegetables — paper-thin raw or lightly cured radish/turnip/beet slices dressed simply.
20 Moorish or North African roasted pepper salad — smoky peppers with garlic, olive oil, and preserved lemon.
21 Marinated mushroom salad — quick-marinated mushrooms with herbs, garlic, and acidic balance.
22 Zucchini ribbon salad — thin ribbons raw or blanched, with lemon, herbs, and a light oil.
23 Warm lentil and roasted vegetable salad — hearty base of lentils paired with roast veg and vinaigrette (legumes + veg).
24 Braised artichoke salad — tender artichokes with lemon, herbs, and olive oil, served warm or cold.
25 Corn and tomato succotash salad — fresh corn, tomatoes, peppers, herbs — summer staple.
26 Japanese sunomono cucumber salad — thin cucumber slices dressed in rice vinegar, optionally with wakame.
27 Asian-style shredded vegetable salad — daikon/carrot/pepper ribbons with sesame, soy, and vinegar dressing.
28 Pickled vegetable platter — assorted quick-pickles (carrot, radish, onion, cucumber) used as a composed salad or garnish.


==================================================
LEGUME/BEAN SALADS
==================================================

1 Three Bean Salad — classic cold salad of green beans, wax beans, and kidney beans in a sweet tangy vinaigrette.
2 Mediterranean Chickpea Salad (Pan Mediterranean chana salad) — chickpeas with tomato, cucumber, red onion, herbs, lemon, and olive oil.
3 Israeli Chickpea Salad — finely diced vegetables and herbs with lemon forward dressing; knife skills and balance matter.
4 Niçoise with Beans (haricots verts &/or white beans) — composed salad where beans are a primary structural element.
5 Italian White Bean Salad (Insalata di Fagioli) — cannellini or borlotti with red onion, parsley, olive oil, and sometimes tuna.
6 Warm White Bean and Escarole/Swiss Chard Salad — sautéed greens and warm beans dressed with vinegar and olive oil.
7 French Lentil Salad (Salade de Lentilles du Puy) — peppery Puy lentils with shallot vinaigrette, herbs, sometimes bacon.
8 Warm Lentil and Bacon/Vegetable Salad — lentils tossed warm with soft vegetables or lardons and mustard vinaigrette.
9 Lentil, Roasted Vegetable, and Feta Salad — hearty, meal worthy lentil base with roasted veg and bright acid.
10 Tabbouleh with Chickpeas or Lentils — herb forward salad where legumes add heft (regional variations).
11 Balela (Levantine Black Bean/Chickpea Salad) — chickpeas and/or black beans with tomatoes, parsley, cumin, and lemon.
12 Black Bean and Corn Salad (Mexican style) — black beans, corn, peppers, cilantro, lime; versatile and staple for summer.
13 Black Eyed Pea Salad (Southern / Hoppin’ John inspired) — black eyed peas with pepper, onion, and tangy dressing.
14 Gigantes Salad (Greek Giant Bean Salad) — boiled gigantes (large white beans) tossed simply with tomato, onion, and oregano.
15 Broad Bean (Fava) Salad — young fava beans with mint, pecorino or ricotta salata, lemon and olive oil.
16 Marinated Mushroom & Bean Salad — beans plus marinated mushrooms for umami and texture contrast.
17 Spanish Ensalada de Alubias (White Bean and Tuna/Vegetables) — white beans paired with preserved fish, peppers, or tomatoes.
18 Puy Lentil and Goat Cheese Salad — peppery lentils balanced with creamy cheese and sharp vinaigrette.
19 Curried Chickpea Salad — curried mayonnaise or yogurt dressing with celery, apple, or raisin for sweet/savory contrast.
20 Smoky Bean Salad with Charred Vegetables and Romesco — grilled veg and beans finished with a nutty red pepper sauce.


==================================================
PASTA SALADS
==================================================

1 Classic American Deli Pasta Salad — tri color rotini, mayonnaise or creamy dressing, peas, carrots, celery, and diced cheese.
2 Italian Antipasto Pasta Salad — short pasta with salami/prosciutto, mozzarella or provolone, roasted peppers, olives, artichokes, and Italian vinaigrette.
3 Mediterranean Orzo Salad — orzo with cucumber, tomato, red onion, feta, olives, and lemon olive oil dressing.
4 Pasta Puttanesca Salad — cooled pasta tossed with a puttanesca mix: tomatoes, olives, capers, anchovy, garlic, and parsley.
5 Caprese Pasta Salad — pasta with cherry tomatoes, fresh mozzarella, basil, balsamic glaze, and olive oil.
6 Greek Pasta Salad — pasta with cucumber, tomato, red onion, Kalamata olives, feta, oregano, and red wine vinaigrette.
7 Tuna Pasta Salad (Mediterranean or American styles) — pasta with canned tuna, celery/onion, peas or capers, dressed either olive oil/lemon or creamy mayo.
8 Pesto Pasta Salad — short pasta coated in basil pesto with cherry tomatoes, roasted vegetables, or burrata.
9 Cold Carbonara-style Pasta Salad — pasta with pancetta or bacon, pea, shaved pecorino, and a loose, bright dressing inspired by carbonara ingredients.
10 Pasta Niçoise Salad — fusilli or penne with green beans, potatoes, olives, tomatoes, and tuna or boiled eggs, dressed in vinaigrette.
11 Sicilian Pasta Salad (Pasta fredda alla siciliana) — pasta with eggplant, cherry tomatoes, capers, olives, and ricotta salata.
12 Caesar Pasta Salad — pasta tossed in a Caesar style dressing with romaine, crouton bits, anchovy and Parmesan.
13 Lemon Herb Orzo with Asparagus — bright orzo with lemon, herbs, shaved asparagus, and Parmigiano.
14 Mediterranean Chickpea Pasta Salad — small pasta mixed with chickpeas, cucumber, tomato, herbs, and vinaigrette for protein.
15 Roasted Vegetable Pasta Salad — pasta with roasted zucchini, peppers, eggplant, mushrooms and a garlicky vinaigrette or romesco.
16 Smoked Salmon Pasta Salad — cold pasta with smoked salmon, dill, capers, red onion, and light crème fraîche or yogurt dressing.
17 Creamy Avocado Pasta Salad — pasta tossed with avocado based creamy dressing, lime, cilantro, and crisp veggies.
18 Southwestern Pasta Salad — pasta with black beans, corn, bell peppers, cilantro, avocado, and a lime chipotle or cumin vinaigrette.
19 Cold Spaghetti with Garlic Oil (Aglio e Olio inspired) — chilled spaghetti with garlic oil, parsley, lemon zest, and shaved Pecorino.
20 Cavatappi with Broccoli and Sundried Tomatoes — toothsome pasta with blanched broccoli, sundried tomatoes, olives, and a sharp vinaigrette.
21 Russian style Pasta Salad (Olivier inspired cold pasta variant) — diced vegetables, pickles, eggs, peas, and mayonnaise blended with small pasta shapes.
22 Asian Cold Noodle Salad (wheat pasta / somen style crossover) — wheat pasta with sesame, soy, rice vinegar, scallion, cucumber, and chili oil.
23 Warm Pasta Salad with Lentils and Greens — pasta tossed warm with braised greens, lentils, mustard vinaigrette, and toasted nuts.
24 Cajun Style Pasta Salad — pasta with smoked sausage or chicken, bell pepper, corn, and a spicy Creole style dressing.
25 Pasta Salad with Burrata and Heirloom Tomatoes — simple high quality ingredients: pasta, ripe tomatoes, creamy burrata, basil, olive oil.


==================================================
GRAIN SALADS
==================================================

1 Tabbouleh (Bulgur) — parsley forward Levantine salad with bulgur, tomato, mint, lemon, and olive oil.
2 Couscous Salad (Moroccan / Mediterranean) — pearl or regular couscous with roasted veg, chickpeas, dried fruit, and spice.
3 Israeli Couscous Salad (Ptitim) — large toasted couscous with bright veg, herbs, feta, or preserved lemon.
4 Quinoa Salad — versatile gluten free base paired with roasted veg, beans, herbs, citrus, or feta.
5 Farro Salad — chewy ancient grain salad with roasted vegetables, herbs, lemon, and shaved cheese.
6 Wheat Berry Salad — hearty whole wheat kernels with root veg, apples or pears, nuts, and mustard vinaigrette.
7 Barley Salad (Pearled or Hulled) — nutty barley with mushrooms, herbs, roasted squash, or gremolata.
8 Freekeh Salad — smoky green wheat used cold or warm with pomegranate, herbs, and spiced dressing.
9 Kasha Salad (Toasted Buckwheat) — earthy buckwheat with mushrooms, scallion, herbs, and bright acid.
10 Bulgur Salad (Koofteh / simple cracked wheat variants) — quick bulgur salads distinct from tabbouleh, often with tomato and cucumber.
11 Orzo Grain-style Salad — rice shaped pasta treated like a grain salad with Mediterranean mix ins.
12 Wild Rice Salad — nutty wild rice with dried fruit, nuts, celery, and a citrusy dressing.
13 Black Rice Salad (Forbidden Rice) — visually striking salad with mango, herbs, nuts, and tangy dressing.
14 Mixed Grain Salad (multi grain pilaf chilled) — millet, quinoa, barley or other combination with seasonal veg and herbs.
15 Millet Salad — small grained cereal used cold with citrus, toasted seeds, and fresh herbs.
16 Sorghum Salad — toothsome sorghum with roasted peppers, beans, and bold vinaigrette.
17 Polenta/Cold Corn Salad — cooled grilled or cubed polenta tossed with tomatoes, basil, and olive oil.
18 Lentil + Grain Salads (e.g., lentils with farro or barley) — legume + grain for protein, texture, and heft.
19 Panzanella style Grain Salad — stale bread or barley/couscous that soaks up tomato forward dressing like a bread salad.
20 Spanish Rice Salad (Arroz frío / rice pilaf chilled) — seasoned rice with peppers, peas, herbs, and vinaigrette.
21 Mexican Street Corn + Grain Salad (corn + quinoa/barley) — grilled corn with cilantro, lime, cheese mixed into a grain base.
22 Sushi Rice Salad / Seasoned Short Grain Rice Salad — vinegared rice used cold with cucumber, sesame, and nori.
23 Greek-style Grain Salad (farro or barley with cucumber, tomato, olives, feta) — classic Mediterranean flavors on a chewy grain base.
24 Persian Jeweled Grain Salad (rice or jeweled barley variants) — fruit, nuts, and herbs combined with scented grains.
25 Tunisian or North African Couscous Salad with Harissa — couscous with preserved lemon, harissa, olive, and herb punch.
26 Korean-style Cold Grain Bowls (multigrain or barley with pickled veg) — chilled grains with tangy, spicy banchan components.
27 Breakfast-style Grain Salads (savory quinoa/oats bowls) — savory preparations of grains with herbs, roasted veg, and a poached egg.


==================================================
MIXED PROTEIN SALADS
==================================================

1 Cobb Salad — chopped greens topped with grilled chicken, bacon, hard boiled egg, avocado, tomato, blue cheese.
2 Niçoise Salad — composed salad with tuna (or anchovy), hard boiled egg, potatoes, green beans, olives.
3 Chef’s Salad — mixed greens with sliced turkey, ham, hard boiled egg, cheese, and seasonal veggies.
4 Salad Olivier (Russian Salad) — diced cooked meats (ham, chicken, or bologna), egg, peas, potatoes, and mayo.
5 Antipasto Salad — Italian style platter salad with salumi, fresh/provolone cheeses, marinated vegetables, olives.
6 Cobb Variants (vegetarian/seafood) — keep the structure but swap proteins: smoked salmon + egg, grilled shrimp + bacon, or tofu + tempeh.
7 Crab Louie — West Coast classic with lump crab, hard boiled egg, asparagus or salad greens, and a tangy Louie dressing.
8 Shrimp and Avocado Salad — poached or grilled shrimp paired with avocado, citrus, and often a second protein like crab or smoked salmon.
9 Seafood Medley Salad — chilled mix of shrimp, scallop, crab, calamari, dressed lightly with herbs and citrus.
10 Poke Bowl (mixed sashimi proteins) — Hawaiian/modern composed bowl often combining tuna, salmon, octopus, with vegetables and rice.
11 Gado Gado — Indonesian warm/cold vegetable salad served with mixed proteins like hard boiled egg, tofu, tempeh, sometimes shrimp or chicken, topped with peanut sauce.
12 Yum Woon Sen (Thai Glass Noodle Salad) — glass noodles tossed with shrimp and sliced pork or chicken, lime, chilies, and herbs.
13 Larb with Mixed Meats — Lao/Thai minced meat salad where multiple ground proteins (pork, duck, chicken) are used or combined.
14 Taco Salad (protein mix) — greens or shells topped with seasoned beef, shredded chicken, beans, cheese, and salsa; often mixes proteins.
15 Warm Mixed Protein Grain Salad — grains or lentils tossed with roasted chicken, pancetta or chorizo, and a soft egg.
16 Nicoise style Grain/Bean Salad with Mixed Proteins — beans or grains with tuna, anchovy, and hard boiled egg as co stars.
17 Smoked Fish Platter Salad — assorted smoked fish (salmon, trout, mackerel) presented with potatoes, pickles, and eggs.
18 Mediterranean Mezze Salad (mixed proteins) — grilled halloumi + lamb kebab or roasted chicken over greens with chickpeas and yogurt dressing.
19 Warm Steak and Shrimp Salad (surf and turf salad) — sliced grilled steak paired with seared shrimp over peppery greens and warm vinaigrette.
20 Barbecue Chicken and Pulled Pork Salad — bold BBQ proteins combined with slaw, corn, beans, and a tangy dressing for a hearty composed salad.


==================================================
FRUIT SALADS
==================================================

1 Waldorf Salad — apples, celery, grapes, and walnuts in a light mayo or yogurt dressing.
2 Ambrosia Salad — citrus segments, pineapple, marshmallows, coconut, and whipped cream or yogurt.
3 Fruit Salad (Mixed Fresh Fruit) — seasonal berries, stone fruit, melon, citrus with a honey lime or mint syrup.
4 Macédoine de Fruits — small, uniform dice of mixed fruit, often in a light syrup or liqueur (classic French).
5 Tropical Fruit Salad — mango, pineapple, papaya, and banana with lime, chili, or coconut.
6 Berry Salad with Balsamic or Mint — mixed fresh berries finished with aged balsamic or bright mint oil.
7 Melon and Prosciutto Salad — cantaloupe or honeydew paired with salty prosciutto and a drizzle of olive oil or balsamic.
8 Citrus Salad (Orange and Grapefruit) — segmented citrus with fennel, olives, and a little olive oil or citrus vinaigrette.
9 Strawberry Spinach Salad (fruit + greens crossover) — strawberries, baby spinach, nuts, and a poppyseed or balsamic dressing.
10 Peach Caprese / Burrata & Peach Salad — ripe peaches with burrata or fresh mozzarella, basil, and olive oil.
11 Grilled Fruit Salad — charred peaches, pineapple, or figs with honey, yogurt, or mascarpone.
12 Poached Pear Salad — pears poached in wine or spiced syrup, served chilled with nuts and cheese.
13 Apple and Endive Salad — tart apples with frisée or endive, blue cheese, and a sherry vinaigrette.
14 Fig and Prosciutto Salad — fresh figs, prosciutto, arugula, and a honey balsamic finish.
15 Salade de Fruits à la Vanille (Vanilla scented fruit salad) — mixed fruit lightly macerated with vanilla and citrus.
16 Mango and Avocado Salad — sweet mango with creamy avocado, lime, cilantro, and chili flakes.
17 Fruit Salsa — diced mango, pineapple, and strawberry with lime and jalapeño; served with chips or fish.
18 Compote-style Fruit Salad — slow cooked mixed fruit served warm or chilled, often with spices.
19 Greek Yogurt and Fruit Parfait Salad — layered fruit with yogurt, granola, and a honey drizzle.
20 Fruit Salad with Liqueur (e.g., kirsch or Cointreau) — macerated seasonal fruit with a splash of spirit.
21 Jellied Fruit Salad (classic retro style) — fruit set in gelatin, sometimes with marshmallows or nuts.
22 Persian Fruit Salad (Faloodeh style elements) — seasonal fruit with rosewater, lime, and chopped pistachio.
23 Tropical Fruit Curry Salad — fruit (mango, apple) tossed with mild curry mayo or yogurt for savory sweet contrast.
24 Spiced Fruit Chaat (Indian fruit salad) — mixed fruit with chaat masala, lemon, and sometimes toasted seeds.
25 Fruit and Cheese Platter Salad — composed bites of fruit paired with varied cheeses, nuts, and honey.



